<h2>First Test Race Complete.</h2>

<table><tr><td bgcolor='$!data.voicecolor'><i>
So, to review: In each of six independent car races, you will be able to bet up to the full amount of money you've earned in the cross-sums task 
on one car winning the race.  The rest of the money will be invested in a better engine for your car.
Each race will consist of 10 laps, and will include three pit stops - after laps 3, 6, and 9 - at which you'll be 
asked some questions and will also have 
the chance to drop out of the bet. You will be actually paid out for the results of one of the six races, chosen randomly.
</i></td></tr></table>

<p>Please let an experiment administrator know (by raising your hand) if you have any questions. </p>

<p>When you're ready, you can click 'Continue', and you will participate in another test race 
up to the last pitstop. This time, the race will be as similar to the real race as possible,
and you won't hear a voiceover - but it's still just a test race.  The top three cars will each lead at some point in the race.
The top three cars will each lead at some point
in the race.  The middle car will be in first position at the first pit stop,
the top car will lead at the second pit stop and the top car will also lead at the third pit stop. The finish of this race will not be shown.</p> 

<p><mp3 name='testrace_race' file='oetinvest/media/tr10_summary.mp3' button='Continue'></p>
